# 6. 大切な時間

Little Shizuku: Stick in the needle, pull down and...
Grandmother: Yes, very good. Next, you need to get the needle back out.
Little Shizuku: Okay...!
Little Shizuku: In, out... In, out...
Little Shizuku: Oh, Grandma, look! My bunny has a whisker now...!
Grandmother: Look at that! And what a whisker it is.
Little Shizuku: Hehe...
Little Shizuku: Oh, I think I'll give this to Shii if it turns out okay.
Grandmother: Hehe. She loves rabbits, so I'm sure she'll love it.
Little Shizuku: You think so? Then, I'm going to make the cutest bunny I can for her!
Little Shizuku: (Oh, my bunny's ears are slowly coming together...)
Little Shizuku: (Hehe. This pink thread's so cute... I hope Shii likes what I'm making for her...)
Little Shizuku: (I want to show her as soon as I can.)
Little Shizuku: (Oh, but I don't want it to get crooked. I need to go slow and steady...)
Little Shizuku: (So that Shii will smile and say that it's cute...)
Grandmother: Hehe...
Little Shizuku: Is something wrong, Grandma?
Grandmother: No, I just noticed how much you're smiling.
Grandmother: Are you enjoying embroidering?
Little Shizuku: Yes! Making the lines is fun, and my chest feels so warm for some reason...
Grandmother: I see. Then, that means you and I are peas in a pod, aren't we?
Little Shizuku: We are...? Oh...
Grandmother: Really? The joy I'm feeling must be overflowing.
Grandmother: After all, I treasure every minute that I spend embroidering.
Little Shizuku: (She felt this same warmth...?)
Little Shizuku: (I'm still getting used to this...)
Little Shizuku: (But I think I really like spending time embroidering...)
Shizuku: I remember Shii being so happy when I gave her the bunny handkerchief I made for her...
Shizuku: After that, I fell even more in love with embroidery.
Mafuyu: I see. That's such a beautiful story.
Shizuku: Hehe. Thank you.
Shizuku: Even now, I'm reminded of the things my grandmother told me whenever I'm embroidering something.
Shizuku: That the time you take and the thoughts you put into each stitch for someone are very precious things...
Shizuku: Also, that having people we care about enough to want to make gifts for them is such a blessing.
Shizuku: That's why I enjoy embroidering things for others so much, and treasure every minute of it.
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: I see. I never thought about it like that...
Shizuku: Oh, but these are just my personal beliefs...
Shizuku: Some people simply enjoy crafting beautiful objects, while others enjoy the quiet time spent focusing. We're all allowed to enjoy embroidery however we like.
Shizuku: Including you, Asahina. My hope is that you'll get to freely express yourself through embroidery.
Mafuyu: Yes, thank you. I'll try to discover what I enjoy the most about the activity.
Shizuku: Wonderful...!
Shizuku: Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to talk for so long.
Mafuyu: No, I really appreciate you telling me that story about when you were little. Anyway, let's get back to work, shall we?
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (We're all allowed to enjoy embroidery however we like...)
Mafuyu: (I do sort of understand the appeal of working on something like this in peace...)
Mafuyu: (And using my own two hands to make something is somewhat soothing...)
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: ...
